Several Palestinian leaders, including Mahmud Abbas, are expected in Paris the following day.
Arafat's wife criticizes the leaders visiting her husband, accusing them of power-grabbing.
Arafat is allowed to leave his headquarters for medical treatment in France.
Conflicting reports on Arafat's condition emerge, with some claiming his death.
Israeli and Palestinian officials reach an agreement on funeral arrangements.
Arafat's burial location remains uncertain.
Egypt offers to host a funeral service for Arafat to spare Arab leaders from Israeli security measures.
The announcement of Arafat's passing is expected the following morning.
